    "Traditional HMIs highly depend on operators' and supervisors' capacity to master manufacturing device operations.With new industrial revolutions and increasing technological advancements, HMIs are becoming more complex due to the large number of factory devices to control and Fig. 12 Prompt and answer 3 predictive maintenance generative AI functionmonitor [46].",
    "Although software engineers are still trying to design supervisory control and data acquisition (SCADA) to show the best possible details to users, the system complexity requires special training and more efforts from operators to understand displayed information, icons, signs, interpret messages and act upon them.In the context of Industry 5.0, the role of an HMI is completely changing [47] from simple SCADA control and monitoring tools to more interactive platforms that operators can utilize efficiently to interpret helpful data for the plant.",
    "We develop a customized chatbot acting as an I5.0 HMI with several benefits over traditional HMIs, such as the ability to:• Learn historical information from the factory and concisely present it upon request.",
    "We achieve this advantage by training the GPT 3.5 LM with a factory CSV file database via a Langchain agent and incorporating the result into the customized chatbot HMI web application.",
    "• Generate new datasets similar to the loaded historical data for AI purposes like ML modelling."
